      "props": {
        "covers": "How one AI-driven canvas edit works end to end: the fitter derives a disposable layout program from the saved document, the AI proposes structural changes, and the deterministic solver and router turn them into the geometry the AI reviews.",
        "format": "mdx",
        "type": "design",
        "concepts": [
          "layout program",
          "fitter",
          "solver",
          "router",
          "derived view",
          "agent editing loop",
          "canvas-agent"
        ]
      }
    },
    "b-overview-title-1": {
      "id": "b-overview-title-1",
      "flavour": "heading",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "How the AI↔canvas layout system works"
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-lede-2": {
      "id": "b-overview-lede-2",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "children": [],
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The AI works with structure, not pixel coordinates. The canvas document is the single source of truth. The layout program is a derived, disposable view: "
        },
        {
          "insert": "fitSketch",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas-agent/src/pipeline/fit.ts",
              "symbol": "fitSketch"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " reads the saved board fresh for every edit, and the program is thrown away afterward, so it can never go stale. Fit, solve, and routing are deterministic — the same document and program produce the same result every time. The AI is the only judgment in the loop: it decides what should change, and the deterministic tools decide where every pixel and line lands."
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-sequence-heading-3": {
      "id": "b-overview-sequence-heading-3",
      "flavour": "heading",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "One edit, in order"
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-sequence-intro-4": {
      "id": "b-overview-sequence-intro-4",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "children": [],
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "One edit, from your command to the updated board. Solid arrows are calls; dashed arrows are derived views coming back."
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-sequence-mermaid-5": {
      "id": "b-overview-sequence-mermaid-5",
      "flavour": "mermaid",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "title": "One edit, in order",
        "caption": "The AI is the only judgment in the loop. The fitter, solver, and router are deterministic, and the document is the one saved thing."
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "sequenceDiagram\n  participant You\n  participant AI as The AI\n  participant Fitter\n  participant Document\n  participant Solver\n  participant Router\n  You->>AI: your command + what you have selected\n  AI->>Fitter: fit the document\n  Fitter->>Document: read\n  Document-->>Fitter: geometry + intent\n  Fitter-->>AI: the program — identical every time\n  Router-->>AI: a picture of the current board\n  loop repeat until it looks right\n    AI->>Solver: a one-line change to the program\n    Solver->>Document: write geometry + intent — one save\n    Document->>Router: new geometry\n    Router-->>AI: a fresh picture — the AI reviews it\n  end\n  AI-->>You: done — the board updates in front of you"
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-steps-heading-6": {
      "id": "b-overview-steps-heading-6",
      "flavour": "heading",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Reading the diagram"
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-step-command-7": {
      "id": "b-overview-step-command-7",
      "flavour": "list-item",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "ordered": true
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "You say what should change.",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " Your command — plus anything you have selected — tells the AI what you want to accomplish."
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-step-fit-8": {
      "id": "b-overview-step-fit-8",
      "flavour": "list-item",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "ordered": true
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The fitter reads the current board.",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " It turns the saved canvas into the compact layout language: groups, rows, columns, grids, lanes, shared centerlines, and arrows. It does not interpret your command; it gives the AI a structural view of what is already there."
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-step-read-9": {
      "id": "b-overview-step-read-9",
      "flavour": "list-item",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "ordered": true
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The AI reads structure and sees the result.",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " The language explains how the board is organized. A screenshot, SVG, or other rendering shows how it actually looks. The AI uses both views together."
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-step-loop-10": {
      "id": "b-overview-step-loop-10",
      "flavour": "list-item",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "ordered": true
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "It changes, solves, and checks.",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " The AI makes a small change to the language. The solver turns that change into geometry, the router redraws the lines, and a fresh rendering comes back for review. The loop repeats until the board looks right."
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-step-done-11": {
      "id": "b-overview-step-done-11",
      "flavour": "list-item",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "ordered": true
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The AI tells you it is done.",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " When the structure and the rendered result both look right, the AI stops iterating and returns the finished board."
        }
      ]
    },
    "b-overview-handoff-observation-12": {
      "id": "b-overview-handoff-observation-12",
      "flavour": "observation",
      "children": [],
      "props": {
        "title": "The handoff is simple"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The fitter reads. The AI decides. The solver places. The router draws."
        }
      ]
    },
